cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper focuses on improving performance of modern high-performance out-of-order cores by addressing the issue of high main memory latency. This falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and specifically prefetching (cs.PF) and memory hierarchy (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the need for dynamic adaptation to available bandwidth, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a novel approach to prefetching using bit-patterns, which could also fall under programming languages (cs.PL) as it involves representing program accesses as bit-patterns.
